<div class="info-section">
  <p>
    Rofo was started in 2007 with a simple goal:
    make it easier for businesses to find the right space.
  </p>

  <p>
    At the time, commercial real estate was difficult to navigate.
    Listings were fragmented, information was inconsistent, and the process often felt opaque.
  </p>

  <p>
    Rofo set out to organize that information — and make it accessible.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="info-section">
  <h2>What Rofo is today</h2>

  <p>
    Today, Rofo is a commercial real estate discovery platform.
  </p>

  <p>
    We focus on helping businesses explore markets, understand their options,
    and identify buildings worth considering — whether you're looking for office, retail, or industrial space.
  </p>

  <p>
    We are not a brokerage.<br>
    We don’t represent landlords or tenants.
  </p>

  <p>
    Instead, we aim to be a neutral starting point —
    a place to research, compare, and get oriented before taking the next step.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="info-section">
  <h2>How we think about the product</h2>

  <p>
    We believe finding space should feel more like exploration and less like friction.
  </p>

  <p>That means:</p>

  <ul class="info-list">
    <li>Clear, structured information</li>
    <li>Useful context about markets and buildings</li>
    <li>A fast, simple experience without unnecessary clutter</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Rofo is designed to be lightweight, practical, and helpful —
    not overwhelming.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="info-section">
  <h2>A note from the founder</h2>

  <p>
    I started Rofo in 2007 after seeing how difficult it was for businesses
    to find and evaluate commercial space.
  </p>

  <p>
    There was plenty of information — but very little of it felt clear or accessible.
  </p>

  <p>
    Rofo was built to simplify that process.
  </p>

  <p>
    Over time, the product has evolved, but the core idea hasn’t changed:
    make it easier to explore, understand, and move forward with confidence.
  </p>

